<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">

    <!--
      SUPPRESSION POLICY
      ══════════════════
      Permanent suppressions are NEVER used. All entries carry an `until` expiry date.
      When the date passes OWASP DC re-flags the CVE automatically, forcing a fresh review.

      Review process when a suppression expires:
        1. Check if a fixed version has shipped — upgrade if so, remove suppression.
        2. If still no fix: re-assess risk, extend `until` by 90 days, update notes.
        3. If CVE does not actually affect this project: document why in notes, extend 90 days.

      2026-07-07 review: all entries (log4j CVE-2025-68161; Azure SDK CVE-2026-33117;
      Netty CVE-2026-42578..42582; CPE false positives CVE-2023-36415 / CVE-2024-35255)
      expired on 2026-07-05 and were removed. The 2026-07-07 main-branch Security Scan ran
      dependencyCheckAll with the expired (hence inactive) suppressions and reported zero
      findings against azure-identity 1.18.4 / netty 4.1.135 — every entry was dead weight.

      2026-07-12 (Sunday cron): Security Scan #29177879526 failed the CVSS>=7.0 gate on
      :benchmarks:dependencyCheckAnalyze. All findings are transitive via
      azure-security-keyvault-secrets (:schema, Azure Key Vault remote-seed source). NB the
      NVD "Update" step timed out at 20 min in that run, so analysis used the restored cache
      rather than a same-day NVD refresh.

      Triage against upstream CVE docs (OSV + NVD):
        - CVE-2026-54428 / CVE-2026-54399 (httpcore5-h2 5.4): REAL, fixed in 5.4.3. Handled by
          forcing httpcore5-h2:5.4.3 in build.gradle.kts — NOT suppressed.
        - CVE-2026-54428 / CVE-2026-54399 vs httpcore 4.4.16 (classic): false positive. The
          HPACK/HTTP2 issue is httpcore5-h2 only; OSV lists only 5.x affected versions; 4.4.16
          is the EOL final 4.x release with no fix and no HTTP/2 support.
        - CVE-2026-33117: false positive. NVD scopes the flaw to the Azure Key Vault *Keys*
          local-crypto path (azure-security-keyvault-keys < 4.10.6). This project uses
          keyvault-*secrets*, not keys; the umbrella cpe:microsoft:azure_sdk_for_java match
          over-matches azure-core/identity/json by their own artifact versions.
        - CVE-2023-36415 / CVE-2024-35255: CPE false positives (confirmed in 2026-07-07 review).

      Suppressions below are all false positives, time-boxed to 2026-10-10.
    -->

    <suppress until="2026-10-10Z">
        <notes>CVE-2023-36415 / CVE-2024-35255: over-broad NVD CPE match against
        cpe:microsoft:azure_identity_sdk and cpe:microsoft:authentication_library. Confirmed
        CPE false positives in the 2026-07-07 review — azure-identity 1.18.4 and msal4j 1.23.1
        are past the affected ranges. Re-verify the CPE mapping at expiry.</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/com\.azure/azure-identity@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2023-36415</cve>
        <cve>CVE-2024-35255</cve>
    </suppress>

    <suppress until="2026-10-10Z">
        <notes>CVE-2024-35255: same CPE false positive as above, matched on msal4j
        (cpe:microsoft:authentication_library). msal4j 1.23.1 is past the affected range.</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/com\.microsoft\.azure/msal4j@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2024-35255</cve>
    </suppress>

    <suppress until="2026-10-10Z">
        <notes>CVE-2026-33117: false positive. NVD scopes this to the Azure Key Vault *Keys*
        local cryptographic verification path (azure-security-keyvault-keys, fixed &lt; 4.10.6).
        This project depends on azure-security-keyvault-*secrets*, not keys, so the vulnerable
        code path is never present. The finding comes from the umbrella
        cpe:microsoft:azure_sdk_for_java match flagging azure-core/identity/json by their own
        (unrelated) artifact versions. Re-verify component + CPE at expiry.</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/com\.azure/azure-(core|core-http-netty|identity|json)@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-33117</cve>
    </suppress>

    <suppress until="2026-10-10Z">
        <notes>CVE-2026-54428 / CVE-2026-54399: false positive on Apache HttpComponents httpcore
        4.4.16 (classic 4.x, transitive via azure-identity -> msal4j). Both CVEs are HTTP/2 /
        header-parsing hardening in httpcomponents-core 5.x (fixed 5.4.3); OSV lists only 5.x
        affected versions. httpcore 4.4.16 is the EOL final 4.x release, has no HTTP/2 support,
        and no fix exists or is needed. The genuinely-affected httpcore5-h2 is upgraded to 5.4.3
        via resolutionStrategy.force in build.gradle.kts (not suppressed).</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.apache\.httpcomponents/httpcore@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-54399</cve>
        <cve>CVE-2026-54428</cve>
    </suppress>

</suppressions>
